Manual VS Automated Testing

Manual:
	Cons
	- Human errors
	- Time consuming
	- Limitations(load, performance testing)
	Pros
	- Live testing
	- UI & UX issues
	- Less investment(tolls, skills)
	- Flexible 
	Usage:
	- Usability testing
	- Ad-hoc testing
	- Non-repetitive tests


Automated:
	Cons:
	- High cost
	- Can't detect UI & UX issues
	- Tools limitation
	Pros:
	- Quik result
	- Reusability
	- Less errors
	- Collaboration
	Usage:
	- Regression Testing
	- Load Testing
	- Performance testing
